{"TopicId":132329,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"55 Cancri e is hot and dry","CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T13:43:13Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T13:43:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://arxiv.org/abs/1511.08901\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAccording to Hubble data\u003C/a\u003E, a super-Earth 55 Cancri e (2 M\u003Csub\u003EEarth\u003C/sub\u003E) appears to have dry atmosphere without free Oxygen or Water, but rich with Hydrogen, Carbon and Nitrogen and containing CO, CO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E and C\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003EH\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s 2000 K hot and revolves around its star every 18 hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(For me, it looks like remains of Jupiter-like gas giant.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-17T13:45:12Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2016 01:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T17:16:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222414745\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455716593\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://arxiv.org/abs/1511.08901\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAccording to Hubble data\u003C/a\u003E, a super-Earth 55 Cancri e (2 M\u003Csub\u003EEarth\u003C/sub\u003E) appears to have dry atmosphere without free Oxygen or Water, but rich with Hydrogen, Carbon and Nitrogen and containing CO, CO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E and C\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003EH\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s 2000 K hot and revolves around its star every 18 hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(For me, it looks like remains of Jupiter-like gas giant.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2 M Earth is too small for a Gas Giant core- however, it is probably a carbon planet, formed in a O2 depleted environment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"insert_name","CreatedById":150339,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T17:22:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwow we managed to image the atmosphere of an exoplanet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-17T22:45:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222415086\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455729732\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150339\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022insert_name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, insert_name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwow we managed to image the atmosphere of an exoplanet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t done any research here, but I don\u0027t think it\u0027s that difficult to see what\u0027s in an exoplanetary atmosphere. You just need to be able to get a light spectrum\u00A0from it. Correct me if I\u0027m wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-02-17T22:45:16Z\u0022 title=\u002202/17/2016 10:45  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Findthepin1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jovus","CreatedById":117163,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-02-18T08:50:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222415816\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022132329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221455749105\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022139989\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Findthepin1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Findthepin1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHaven\u0027t done any research here, but I don\u0027t think it\u0027s that difficult to see what\u0027s in an exoplanetary atmosphere. You just need to be able to get a light spectrum\u00A0from it. Correct me if I\u0027m wrong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck getting a photometric reading off the atmosphere when the only way you can even tell if the planet\u0027s there is because it transits its sun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s definitely not impossible, but it\u0027s nothing to sniff at, either.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}